word_group.brief_definition: 在这个星球上；在地球上

bilingual.source: Mars is the fourth planet from the Sun.
bilingual.target: 火星是离太阳第四颗行星。

bilingual.source: The earth is a planet and it goes around the sun.
bilingual.target: 地球是一颗行星，它绕着太阳转。
每颗行星都有其独特的轨道。

bilingual.source: The orbit of the planet is elliptic.
bilingual.target: 这颗行星的轨道是椭圆的。

bilingual.source: Earth is a planet in the solar system.
bilingual.target: 地球是太阳系中的一颗行星。

bilingual.source: Mercury is the closest planet to the Sun.
bilingual.target: 水星是离太阳最近的行星。

bilingual.source: Saturn is the sixth planet from the Sun.
bilingual.target: 土星是距离太阳第六颗行星。

bilingual.source: Earth is the third planet from the Sun.
bilingual.target: 地球是距离太阳第三近的行星。

list.abstract: 行星（英文：Planet）通常指自身不发光，环绕着恒星的天体，名字来自于它们的位置在天空中不固定，就好像在行走一般。 其公转方向常与所绕恒星的自转方向相同。一般来说，行星需具有一定质量，行星的质量要足够的大且近似于圆球状，自身不能像恒星那样发生核聚变反应。

yingyinNormal.en: Honey? Peaches? Pluto is not a planet anymore.
yingyinNormal.zh: 亲爱的，小亲亲，冥王星已经不再是行星了。

yingyinNormal.en: Such as external planet and the planet likely to develop life N=R*Fp*Ne*Fl*Fi*Fc*L. Yeah, that one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 比如具有行星的星系或者有生命存在的行星N=R*Fp*Ne*Fl*Fi*Fc*L。对，就是那个。

yingyinNormal.en: Five, four, three, two, one, blast off! We live on a planet. Does anyone know what it is called? The Earth.
yingyinNormal.zh: 五，四，三，二，一，发射！我们住在行星上，大家知道这个行星叫什么吗？叫地球。

yingyinNormal.en: This water was called the ocean. An ocean planet was born.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们称这盐水为海洋，于是海洋行星就诞生了。

yingyinNormal.en: Every planet orbiting a luminous object is casting a shadow out into space.
yingyinNormal.zh: 绕着恒星运行的每一个行星，都会向太空投射阴影。

yingyinNormal.en: They made a scientific discovery that pluto's not a planet anymore. Will you be okay?
yingyinNormal.zh: 科学家们的最新发现表明冥王星其实并不是行星。你还好吧？

yingyinNormal.en: What's the difference? Dancing cats and a new planet are just gonna get replaced by something new tomorrow.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有什么关系呢？跳舞猫和新行星明天就会被新东西替代。

yingyinNormal.en: It can be difficult for Terrsies, or people from underdeveloped worlds, to hear that their planet is not the only inhabited planet in the verse.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对来自未开化世界的人来说或许很难理解，当他们发现自己的星球并非是唯一有生命的行星。

yingyinNormal.en: I think it's a little early for Mercury to be visible yet. Playing hard to get. I like that in a planet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在要看到水星还太早了点吧。玩欲擒故纵。我就喜欢这样的行星。

yingyinNormal.en: What we've learned so far is that literally every star in the galaxy has at least one planet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 迄今为止，我们了解到的是差不多银河系里的每个恒星，都有至少一个行星。

yingyinNormal.en: Two hundred light-years away, there is a Saturn-size planet orbiting, not one, but two stars.
yingyinNormal.zh: 距离两百光年的地方，有一颗土星大小的行星绕着，不是一颗，而是两颗恒星运行。

yingyinNormal.en: Everybody knows that. Pluto's a little cutie-pie. The smallest planet with the biggest heart.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大家都知道这一点。冥王星就是个小可爱。虽是最小的行星，却有着最大的一颗心。

yingyinNormal.en: There's not a planet in our solar system that could sustain life and the nearest star's over a thousand years away.
yingyinNormal.zh: 太阳系没有适合人类生存的星球，系外最近的行星却在一千光年之外。

yingyinNormal.en: Ma'am, we need to approach the planet in the direction it's moving. That way, we benefit from its energy of motion.
yingyinNormal.zh: 长官，我们应顺着其运行方向接近这颗行星，这样就能充分利用其动能。

yingyinNormal.en: Titus, didn't you bother to look at the sheaves? That planet is worth more than all of your estates combined.
yingyinNormal.zh: 泰塔斯 你哥哥不可能不知道？那颗行星的价值比你所有的财产加起来都大。

yingyinNormal.en: How do you slingshot your forces into an attack position on the blind side of this moon using the gravitational pull from this planet?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们该如何利用来自行星的引力，把战力输送到卫星背面抢占有利于进攻的位置？

yingyinNormal.en: Come on, you do it to feel superior. I see that twinkle in your eye when someone says "who" instead of "whom" or thinks the moon is a planet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拜托，你只是给自己带来优越感，每次有人犯语法错误或是把月亮当作行星时，我都能看到你两眼放光。

yingyinNormal.en: Compared to what? The idea that you're the only intelligent species, on the only inhabitable planet in a universe so full of planets that you don't even have a number to describe how many there are?
yingyinNormal.zh: 与什么相比？尤其是当宇宙中充满无数行星，数量多到在你们的世界都没有单位可以描述。

yingyinNormal.en: You know I get sentimental, and I was going through some of Mother's old sheave-work and I came across a description of a planet she claimed was the most rare and beautiful estate she ever owned.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道我很多愁善感，我在整理妈妈从前工作的时候发现了一颗行星，曾经被妈妈称为她拥有过的最罕见最美丽的地方。

yingyinNormal.en: But we're more than that. We are, but no one knows that if the dancing cat videos have a billion views and the discovery of a new planet only gets 27,000 likes. All me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但我们不止如此。我们就是这样，但是没人知道的是跳舞猫有十亿浏览量而发现了一颗新行星却只能得到27000个赞。都是我点的。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: He hasn't stopped reading yet — not even after becoming one of the most successful people on the <highlight>planet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他没有停止阅读，甚至在他成为地球上最成功的人士之一后，仍旧没有停下来。

examination_example.sentence: Rested in the Pacific Ocean, Mauna Kea's peak rises above the bulk of our <highlight>planet</highlight>'s dense atmosphere.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 莫纳克亚山坐落在太平洋上，它的顶峰高耸于地球稠密的大气层之上。

examination_example.sentence: We have now identified enough of the long-term patterns shaping the history of the <highlight>planet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们现在已经确定了足够多的塑造地球历史的长期模式。

examination_example.sentence: Made up of a series of white skulls, the painting reminds drivers of the effect their pollution is having on the <highlight>planet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这幅由一系列的白色的头骨组成的画提醒司机污染对地球的影响。

examination_example.sentence: And isn't this the generation who say they're concerned about their health and the well-being of the <highlight>planet</highlight>?

examination_example.sentence: We have looked at our <highlight>planet</highlight> from every angle and found all of the wildest things left to find.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们从各个角度观察了我们的星球，发现了所有尚未发现的最狂野的东西。

examination_example.sentence: There was a bit of me that didn't want to love this when everyone else on the <highlight>planet</highlight> did.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当这个星球的其他人都喜欢它时，我有一点不喜欢它。
